\begin_layout Enumerate

\shape smallcaps
Demand of a product (
\shape default
\emph on
Total credits: 11p
\shape smallcaps
\emph default
)
\shape default

\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset VSpace medskip
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Problem (a) should only be solved on 
\series bold
\color blue
Paper
\series default
\color inherit
.
 A company sells a product.
 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{i}=$
\end_inset

 the demanded quantity of the product in month 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

, which is assumed to follow a Poisson distribution: 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{i}\vert\theta\overset{iid}{\sim}\mathrm{Poisson}(\theta)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $p\left(q_{i}|\theta\right)=\left(q_{i}!\right)^{-1}\theta^{q_{i}}e^{-\theta}$
\end_inset

.
 The demanded quantity for five months one year was: 
\begin_inset Formula $q_{1}=322,q_{2}=248,q_{3}=385,q_{4}=341,q_{5}=310$
\end_inset

.
 A Bayesian analysis resulted in the following gamma posterior distribution
 for 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

 with parameters 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{n}=2326$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta_{n}=7$
\end_inset

: 
\begin_inset Formula $p\left(\theta|q_{1},\dots,q_{5}\right)\propto\theta^{\alpha_{n}-1}e^{-\beta_{n}\theta}$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
Credits: 3p.

\emph default
 Derive the prior distribution that was used for 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

.
\series bold
\color blue

\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
Credits: 3p.

\emph default
 Simulate 
\begin_inset Formula $10000$
\end_inset

 draws from the posterior predictive distribution of the demanded quantity
 in the next month, 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{6}$
\end_inset

, and plot a histogram of the draws.
 Compute 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathrm{Pr}(Q_{6}>350\vert q_{1},...,q_{5})$
\end_inset


\series bold
\color blue
 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
Credits: 5p.

\emph default
 The company needs to decide how much of the product to keep in stock for
 the sale in the next month.
 The utility function is of the form
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
u(a,Q_{6})=\begin{cases}
p\cdot Q_{6}-\left(a-Q_{6}\right) & \text{ if }Q_{6}\leq a\\
p\cdot a-0.1\left(Q_{6}-a\right)^{2} & \text{ if }Q_{6}>a
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\color black
where 
\begin_inset Formula $p=15$
\end_inset

 is the sale price for the product and 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 (positive integer) is the stock held for the next month.
 
\color inherit
This utility function is given in the file 
\family typewriter
ExamData.R
\family default
.

\color black
 Use simulation to find the optimal 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 using a Bayesian decision approach.
\series bold
\color blue

\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\series default
\color inherit

\begin_inset VSpace 3cm
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
